casebody.head_matter:
HENRY SCHEIN, INC., et al., applicants,
v.
ARCHER AND WHITE SALES, INC.
No. 17A859.
Supreme Court of the United States
March 2, 2018.
Application for stay presented to Justice ALITO and by him referred to the Court granted, and the proceedings in the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Texas, case No. 2:12-cv-572, are stayed pending the timely filing and disposition of a petition for writ of certiorari. Should the petition for writ of certiorari be denied, this stay shall terminate automatically. In the event the petition for writ of certiorari is granted, the stay shall terminate upon the sending down of the judgment of this Court.
